Then rebuild and reinstall.

My practical recommendation

At this point, I would stop spending time on the network and radio side.

You have already proven:

* the E320 is alive
* the E320 is controllable
* MPM works remotely
* the link is good

So the shortest path forward is:

Option A

Rebuild host UHD cleanly

Option B

If you need progress immediately, run GNU Radio on the E320 itself and move the data off the device afterward or stream processed data to the host.

Bottom line

You have essentially solved the radio/network problem.

The remaining issue is almost certainly a host UHD software issue.

